    <div class="panel">
        <h5>General rule processing overview</h5>

        <p>With the inclusion of a semantic rules processor, the idea is to apply complex semantics to validate specific conditions before, during and after the integration task. This Ruler process works as follows:</p>

        <ol>
            <li>Data gets into the platform for processing (hook/push diff data)</li>

            <li>Data are abstracted to a semantic web environment, using custom ETL rules, and storing the graph in COEUS</li>

            <li>The graph abstraction is sent for rule processing, assessing specific components of the graph</li>

            <li>Once all defined rules pass, the integration is ready for delivery</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
